<paragraph id="CD694124FF908419FF3E5434FD58C9B5" blockId="24.[132,775,603,654]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">
PUBLISHED RECORDS IN 
<collectingCountry id="B5C101B4FF908419FEC85434FDE7C949" box="[370,539,604,629]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">NEW CALEDONIA</collectingCountry>
. — Intentionally introduced in 2003 and 2006 from Australia (
<bibRefCitation id="A9473CD5FF908419FDAC541EFD65C9B5" author="BRINON L." box="[534,665,630,654]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153" refId="ref27285" refString="BRINON L. 2008. - Cactus (Acanthocereus pentagonus) control trials on the south-west coast of New Caledonia. 65 - 66, in BLANFORT V. &amp; ORAPA W. (eds), Ecology, Impacts and Management of Invasive Plant Species in Pastoral Areas. Proceedings, regional workshop on invasive plant species in pastoral areas, 24 - 28 November 2003, Kone, New Caledonia, 201 p." type="book" year="2008">Brinon 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="85CC12AFFF908419FF3E54C4FD89C8C6" pageId="24" pageNumber="153" type="description">
<paragraph id="CD694124FF908419FF3E54C4FEDFC9E6" blockId="24.[132,775,682,733]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">
OTHER RECORDS. — South America, 
<collectingCountry id="B5C101B4FF908419FE4354C2FDAEC9F9" box="[505,594,682,706]" name="Australia" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">Australia</collectingCountry>
, southern Europe, southern Africa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD694124FF908419FF3E5492FD13C82A" blockId="24.[132,751,761,786]" box="[132,751,761,786]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">
HOST- PLANTS IN 
<collectingCountry id="B5C101B4FF908419FE975492FE2AC82B" box="[301,470,762,786]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">NEW CALEDONIA</collectingCountry>
. — 
<taxonomicName id="0AD63AA7FF908419FDB95491FD15C82A" box="[515,745,761,785]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Acanthocereus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetragonus">
<emphasis id="FFA29D36FF908419FDB95491FD15C82A" box="[515,745,761,785]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">Acanthocereus tetragonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD694124FF908419FF3E5546FED9C894" blockId="24.[132,776,813,943]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">
NOTES. — This mealybug was introduced to attempt biological control of the invasive cactus 
<taxonomicName id="0AD63AA7FF908419FE0D5520FDC9C85B" box="[439,565,840,864]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Acanthocereus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="24" pageNumber="153" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetragonus">
<emphasis id="FFA29D36FF908419FE0D5520FDC9C85B" box="[439,565,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">A. tetragonus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but both 2003 and 2006 strains from Queensland did not survive (
<bibRefCitation id="A9473CD5FF908419FDC1550AFCF8C840" author="BRINON L." box="[635,772,866,891]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153" refId="ref27285" refString="BRINON L. 2008. - Cactus (Acanthocereus pentagonus) control trials on the south-west coast of New Caledonia. 65 - 66, in BLANFORT V. &amp; ORAPA W. (eds), Ecology, Impacts and Management of Invasive Plant Species in Pastoral Areas. Proceedings, regional workshop on invasive plant species in pastoral areas, 24 - 28 November 2003, Kone, New Caledonia, 201 p." type="book" year="2008">Brinon 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="A9473CD5FF908419FF3C5515FEBBC8AE" author="GATIMEL B. &amp; CAPLONG P. &amp; JOURDAN H." box="[134,327,893,917]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153" refId="ref28903" refString="GATIMEL B., CAPLONG P. &amp; JOURDAN H. 2010. - Essai de controle biologique du cactus envahissant Acanthocereus tetragonus sur la presqu'ile de Bourake. IRD, DDR Province Sud, rapport final, 37 p." type="book" year="2010">
Gatimel 
<emphasis id="FFA29D36FF908419FF615516FEF7C8AE" box="[219,267,893,917]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
), so the species is considered still absent from 
<collectingCountry id="B5C101B4FF908419FF3E55F0FEDDC894" box="[132,289,919,943]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD694124FF908419FF3E558DFD89C8C6" blockId="24.[132,629,997,1024]" box="[132,629,997,1024]" pageId="24" pageNumber="153">
